      "pronunciation": { "classical": "/m\u025b\u0302\u02d0.nis/" },
      "exampleSentence": "\u039c\u1fc6\u03bd\u03b9\u03bd \u1f04\u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5, \u03b8\u03b5\u03ac.",
      "exampleTranslation": "Sing, goddess, of the wrath.",
      "notes": "Transliteration: m\u0113nin. This is not ordinary anger but divine, catastrophic rage. The very first word of Western literature."
